<br>
Not sure how I even got involved with this guy -- I was running off to solo since I'm the only person in Norrath without LDoN, it seems. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hey, can you help me ? I need a piece for the Can 2 quest.&quot;<br>
<br>
What can I say, I'm a sucker for a shaman, since I used to be one, and if you actually have to hunt down the pieces, that quest is a bitch. <br>
<br>
It didn't start off well since I was lost ( I am ALWAYS lost ), but I had warned him. His groupmates were getting &quot;impatient&quot; although no one in the group ( including me )  was really high enough to get into the part of KC he needed. He spam inspected my gear, bitched that everyone had a FT1 earring before him, and added me to his &quot;badasses to bother list.&quot; ( How many times can one be called a badass before it begins to get annoying ?) Bottom line, group was too low, didn't have the DPS. He kept pushing, but finally got a clue. I think.<br>
<br>
Next night, &quot;Can I borrow some plat ? I have all my funds invested in sellable gear?&quot;  Uh no. <br>
<br>
Many nights after that, I'd get a tell : &quot;Want to join a LDoN group?&quot; Er. No. Just like I've told you for every night for the past week, I don't have LDoN. &quot;You should get it. We need a tank.&quot; Okee. I'll be sure to run out and get that just so I can be your meatshield. NOT.<br>
<br>
And then there was the grouping.... ugh .<br>
<br>
Oh wait this was about beggars wasn't it ?<br>
<br>
Hate them. Especially the ones that won't go away. I had tolerated him because he was a shaman. Pretty much had the last straw tonight.<br>
